<document>
  <properties>
    <title>Installation on Database Derby</title>
  </properties>
  <body>
    <section name="Overview">
      <p>The <a href="http://db.apache.org/derby/">Apache Derby Database</a> is
         the default database used from eFaps out of the box. All needed
         libraries and batch scripts are included and could be used for first
         tests.</p>
      <p>Further information and documentation about Derby could be found on
         the <a href="http://db.apache.org/derby/manuals/">manual page</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section name="Starting Derby Database Server">
      <p>Run the startDB.bat shell script.</p>
    </section>

    <section name="Defining Bootstrap File">
      <p>Copy file bootstrap.xml.template-for-derby to bootstrap.xml.</p>
    </section>

    <section name="Installing eFaps Data Model">
      <p>Run 'shell.bat -create'.</p>
    </section>

  </body>
</document>
